quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  21,82,"And of the devils were some that would dive for him and perform other, lesser tasks, but We were preserving of them."
  21,83,"And Job, when he called upon his Lord: “Great harm has touched me, yet You are the Most Merciful of the merciful.”"
  21,84,"So We responded to him and lifted the harm which had afflicted him, and We brought him his family and their like with them—a mercy from Us, and a reminding for the worshipers."
  21,85,"And Ishmael and Enoch and Ezekiel; each is<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>one of the steadfast.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an speaks about the prophets using present tense; this should be pondered by the reader
  21,86,"And We entered them into Our mercy; indeed, they are<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>of the righteous.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an speaks about the prophets using present tense; this should be pondered by the reader
  21,87,"And Jonah, when he went off angrily and he thought that <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…and he thought that he would not be restrained.”</span>
  21,88,"So We responded to him and delivered him from stress, <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Shu’ba read it as: “…and thus the believers were saved.”</span>
  21,89,"And Zechariah, when he called out to his Lord, “My Lord, do not leave me solitary, while You are the best of inheritors.”"
  21,90,"So We responded to him and granted him John, and We rehabilitated his spouse for him. Indeed, they used to hasten towards good works and call upon Us wishfully and in awe, for they used to be reverent towards Us."
